annotationA: Probable medium-chain specific acyl-CoA dehydrogenase, mitochondrial; This enzyme is specific for acyl chain lengths of 4 to 16; Belongs to the acyl-CoA dehydrogenase family
annotationB: Mitochondrial trifunctional protein alpha subunit, isoform A; enoyl-CoA hydratase activity; long-chain-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity; coenzyme binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: determination of adult lifespan; response to starvation; fatty acid beta-oxidation; wound healing
